_refine.details                                  
;The Clusterin construct is a glyco-protein, which was expressed in the presence of the alpha-mannosidase I inhibitor kifunensine, which prevents trimming of mannose moieties, resulting in oligo-mannose N-glycans, and thereby prevents processing to mature complex N-glycans (Chang et al., Structure 15, 267(2007), Fig. 1B).  Asn residues 86, 103, 145, 291, 354 and 374 are expected to carry predominantly NAG-NAG-BMA-(3->1)MAN-MAN-MAN (6->1)-MAN (3->1)MAN-MAN (6->1)MAN-MAN N-glycan trees (Chang et al., Structure 15, 267(2007), Fig. 1B).
;
